; greedy-decode.fk — greedy argmax over logits: the SELECTION half of the autoregressive generation
; loop, the other half of the body kv-cache.fk (#3382) realizes for the ATTENTION half.
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk
;
; In temperature-0 (greedy) decode, the next token is simply the argmax of the model's final logit
; vector over the vocabulary: the index of the largest logit wins. This lived ONLY inside
; transformer-kernel.fk's tk-emit-llama as emitted C —
;     for (int t = 1; t < V; t++) if (logits[t] > logits[best]) best = t;
; — never a standalone proven recipe, exactly like the llama numerics (#3308), RoPE (#3319), the
; block (#3346), and the KV cache (#3382) before they were lifted. This lifts the selection step to a
; Form recipe on the four-kernel floor.
;
; The load-bearing semantic is the TIE RULE: the emitted C replaces the incumbent only on a STRICTLY
; greater logit (`>`, not `>=`), so when two logits tie, the FIRST-seen (lowest index) token wins. A
; deterministic decoder must reproduce that exactly, or two correct kernels would pick different
; tokens from identical logits. gd-argmax walks the vector ascending and replaces the best only on
; `gt` (strictly greater) — bit-for-bit the emitted-C rule. Logits are unbounded reals (often all
; negative after the classifier), so the comparison must hold across the sign boundary; the band pins
; that with an all-negative case.
;
; This is the SAME max-select-by-index spine the body already runs in histogram-peak.fk (hp-peak-loop,
; over integer bin counts), nearest-shape.fk (ns-best, most-agreement-wins), and sequence-predictor.fk
; (sp-predict, most-followers-wins) — only here the score is a float LOGIT and the candidates are token
; indices. The band PROVES the consolidation: gd-argmax over a float vector equals hp-peak-bin
; bit-for-bit, so this is the decoder-altitude name for one already-proven spine, not a fourth copy.
; NAMED core-lift follow-up: fold hp-peak-loop / ns-best / sp-predict onto one generic argmax-by-index
; primitive (the gt-not-ge, seed-index-0, walk-ascending shape they all share) and let each domain be
; the thin score-source over it.
;
; This lives at the reusable decoder-engine altitude (like kv-cache.fk's kv-generate, #3382): any
; model that emits logits decodes greedily through the same selection.
;
; Proven by: form-stdlib/tests/greedy-decode-band.fk
; teaching: lc-cognitive-sovereignty

; --- MAX-SELECT over INDICES: carry the best index + its logit; a STRICTLY-greater logit replaces them
;     (gt, not ge), so on a tie the earlier/lower index stays — bit-for-bit the emitted-C `>` rule.
;     Walk ascending, stop when i reaches the length. Same spine as hp-peak-loop / ns-best-loop. ---
(defn gd-argmax-loop (xs i best-i best-v)
  (if (eq i (len xs)) best-i
      (if (gt (nth xs i) best-v)
          (gd-argmax-loop xs (add i 1) i (nth xs i))
          (gd-argmax-loop xs (add i 1) best-i best-v))))

; --- ARGMAX INDEX: the token index of the largest logit, ties to the lowest index. Seed with index 0
;     as the incumbent, then walk from index 1 — index 0 holds on any tie. ---
(defn gd-argmax (xs) (gd-argmax-loop xs 1 0 (nth xs 0)))

; --- GREEDY TOKEN: the decoder name — the next token is the argmax of the logit vector. ---
(defn gd-token (logits) (gd-argmax logits))
